  "expected_persona": "creator",
  "expected_tool": "create_task",

  "classification": {
    "raw_llm_response": "...",
    "parsed_persona": "creator",
    "correct": True,
    "error": None,
  },

  "tool_calling": {
    "steps": [
      {"action": "create_task", "action_input": {...}, "observation": "..."}
    ],
    "tools_called": ["create_task"],
    "expected_tool_called": True,
    "parse_error_count": 0,
    "final_answer": "...",
    "error": None,
  },

  "verdict": "PASS" | "PARTIAL" | "FAIL",
  "verdict_reason": "...",
}

Verdict logic:
- PASS: classification correct AND expected tool called AND 0 parse errors
- PARTIAL: classification correct BUT tool not called OR wrong tool OR parse errors
- FAIL: classification wrong OR exception

